BILL NO. 36-0024
Thirty-Sixth Legislature of the Virgin Islands
February 27, 2025
An Act amending title 14 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 85 by adding section 1710 declaring a
person incapable of consent to sexual relations while the person is in police custody
PROPOSED BY: Senator Ray Fonseca
Co-sponsor: Milton E. Potter
1 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the Virgin Islands:
2 SECTION 1. Title 14 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 85 is amended by adding section
3 1710 as follows:
4 “§ 1710. Consent; victim in police custody
5 (a) A person is incapable of consent to sexual relations when the person is
6 detained, including traffic stops and questioning pursuant to an investigation, under
7 arrest, or is otherwise in the custody of a police officer or other law enforcement official,
8 and the offender is a police officer or other law enforcement official who either:
9 (1) detained or arrested the person or is responsible for the person’s
10 custody; or

2
1 (2) knows or should reasonably know that the person is under arrest or in
2 custody.
3 (b) As used in this section:
4 (1) “Law enforcement official” means a person who is responsible for the
5 prevention, investigation, apprehension or detention of individuals suspected or
6 convicted of offenses against the criminal laws, including a peace officer
7 empowered to enforce the law through peace officer standards and training
8 certification.
9 (2) “Sexual relations” means sexual contact, sexual intercourse, or sodomy
10 as defined in section 1699 of this chapter.”
11 BILL SUMMARY
12 This bill amends title 14 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 85 by adding section 1710
13 declaring a person incapable of consent to sexual relations when the person is in the custody of
14 a police officer or other law enforcement official who is either responsible for the person’s
15 custody or knows or should reasonably know that the person is in custody.
